🧩 Core Idea (CFM applied)

We treat a prompt as:

Field = possible interpretations
Gates = constraints (intent, style, usefulness)
Moves = refinements
Lock = best prompt form

Instead of guessing what to write…
we filter and evolve prompts until they stabilize

⸻

⚙️ The System

Step 1 — Expand (Field)

Take your input and generate candidate interpretations:

Example input:

“make me a workout”

Field:

{
 [general-workout],
 [bodybuilding],
 [fat-loss],
 [athletic-performance],
 [minimal-equipment],
 [home-workout]
}


⸻

Step 2 — Gate (Filter)

Apply constraints:

|> specific
|> actionable
|> aligned-with-user-context
|> high ROI

Weak candidates die off.

⸻

Step 3 — Refine (Moves)

Transform survivors:

[general-workout]
 -> [structured 4-day hypertrophy plan]
 -> [push/pull/legs split with progression]
 -> [time-efficient hypertrophy plan]


⸻

Step 4 — Lock (Best Prompt)

Final output:

"Create a 4-day hypertrophy workout focused on building size and strength, using minimal equipment, with progressive overload and 60-minute sessions."


